    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <!-- UTILITY CLASSES -->
        <a name="utility"><h1>Utility classes</h1></a>
        <p>Utility classes don't necessarily show on the page but aid other classes to achieve a specific style. Most of these can be used on their own as well as in combination with other classes.</p>
        <h2>Dotted line</h2>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "dotted_line_example.png", :alt => "Dotted line example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a dotted line</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-split-line
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Margin</h2>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Adds or removes some margin</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-margin-top-3
.s3d-margin-top-5
.s3d-margin-top-10
.s3d-margin-top-15
.s3d-margin-top-20
.s3d-button.s3d-margin-top-5
.s3d-button.s3d-no-margin-top
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Hide elements</h2>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Hide an element</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-hidden
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Bold text</h2>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Make text bold</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-bold
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Floats</h2>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create floating elements</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.fl-force-left
.fl-force-right
</pre>
        </div>


        <!-- ACCESSIBILITY -->
        <a name="accessibility"><h1>Accessibility</h1></a>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Apply to containers that need to be rendered off-screen but visible to screen readers</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-aural-text
</pre>
        </div>


        <!-- LINKS -->
        <a name="links"><h1>Links</h1></a>
        <h2>Regular links</h2>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "regular_links_example.png", :alt => "Regular links example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a regular link</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
<span class="blue">&lt;a href=<span class="green">"http://www.google.co.uk"</span> class=<span class="green">"s3d-regular-links"</span>&gt;<span class="black">www.google.co.uk</span>&lt;/a&gt;</span>
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Button links</h2>
        <p>Button links are regular links that have a button style applied</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "button_link_example.png", :alt => "Button link example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a button link</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
<span class="blue">&lt;a href=<span class="green">"/search#q=query"</span> class=<span class="green">"s3d-button s3d-large-button"</span>&gt;<span class="black">__MSG__SHOW_ALL_RESULTS__</span>&lt;/a&gt;</span>
</pre>
        </div>


        <!-- BUTTONS -->
        <a name="buttons"><h1>Buttons</h1></a>
        <h2>General</h2>
        <p>This class has to be applied to all buttons as it contains some overrides for the browser's default button style.</p>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Override default browser button style</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Link buttons</h2>
        <p>Link buttons are buttons that are styled as regular links. They are often used in situations where a pop up is invoked on click instead of browsing to another page.</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "link_button_example.png", :alt => "Link button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Convert a link to a button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-link-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Header buttons</h2>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "header_button_example.png", :alt => "Header button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a header button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-header-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Header buttons (smaller)</h2>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "smaller_header_button_example.png", :alt => "Smaller header button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a smaller header button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-header-button.s3d-header-smaller-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Pop out buttons</h2>
        <p>A 'pop out' button is a button that's based on the default header button. A typical use case would be a button that's floating right on the edge of a container. It's style is different from a normal button as it only has one side of rounded borders in order to make it float on the edge.</p>
        <p>Example pop out button:</p>
        <%= image_tag "popout_button_example.png", :alt => "Pop out button" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a pop out button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-popout-button-shadow
.s3d-button.s3d-header-button.s3d-popout-button

<span class="blue">&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div class=<span class="green">"s3d-popout-button-shadow"</span>&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;button class=<span class="green">"s3d-button s3d-header-button s3d-popout-button"</span> type=<span class="green">"button"</span>&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;<span class="black">+</span>&lt;/span&gt;<span class="black">__MSG__ADD__</span>
    &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Large in-page buttons</h2>
        <p>Large in-page buttons are used to emphasize an action in the UI. An example of this is a 'show more' button to show more results for a search.</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "large_button_example.png", :alt => "Large in-page button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a large in-page button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-large-button
a.s3d-button.s3d-large-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Overlay buttons</h2>
        <p>This type of button is typically used in overlays invoked in the UI but can be used inside of a page as well. They define a 'submit' or 'complete' action (e.g. share content, update profile).</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "overlay_button_example.png", :alt => "Overlay button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create an overlay button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-overlay-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Overlay action buttons</h2>
        <p>This overlay action buttons are only used in overlays to define a 'complete' or 'submit' action.</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "overlay_action_button_example.png", :alt => "Overlay action button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create an overlay action button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-overlay-action-button
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Button without text</h2>
        <p>You can create buttons without text to hold an icon.</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "no_text_button_example.png", :alt => "Button without text example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a button without text</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button.s3d-button-no-text
</pre>
        </div>
        <h2>Button in a button</h2>
        <p>Buttons inside of buttons can be useful when you want to apply a style to the counters that looks like a button and bind actions to buttons inside of that container.</p>
        <p>Example:</p>
        <%= image_tag "button_in_button_example.png", :alt => "Button in a button example" %>
        <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_container few_lines">
            <div class="navigationalitems_codesnippit_header">
                <h4>Create a button in a button</h4>
            </div>
<pre class="black">
.s3d-button .s3d-button-in-button
.s3d-button .s3d-button-in-button-lighter
.s3d-button.s3d-overlay-action-button .s3d-button-in-button
</pre>
        </div>


        <!-- DROP DOWNS -->
